Subject: Rebrand command examples + config paths in the README quickstart

README.md / README.zh-CN.md are engine-excepted (whole-file) so attribution вҖ”
badges, the fork-notice block, upstream docs/LICENSE links, "Hermes Agent"
product references вҖ” survives the rename. But that exception also left the
copy-paste command examples as `hermes ...` and the config paths as `~/.hermes`
/ `%LOCALAPPDATA%\hermes`, while the installed binary is `nadia`
(pyproject `[project.scripts] nadia = ...`) and config lives in ~/.nadia. So every
documented quickstart command was command-not-found and the config path was
wrong вҖ” first-run failure for anyone following the README.

This patch rebrands ONLY the command invocations (`hermes <cmd>` -> `nadia <cmd>`,
`./hermes`, `~/.local/bin/hermes`) and the config-dir paths (~/.hermes ->
~/.nadia, %LOCALAPPDATA%\hermes -> %LOCALAPPDATA%\nadia). It deliberately leaves
attribution intact: the `NousResearch/hermes-agent` repo URLs, the
`hermes-agent.nousresearch.com` docs links, and capital-"Hermes" product prose
are untouched (the rebrand regex `\bhermes\b(?![-/.])` skips `hermes-agent` and
URLs by construction). See tests/test_readme_commands_rebranded.py. IU-AC-4.

